formula.p:
73.--TO PRESERVE APPLES FOR THE YEAR ROUND.
Put them in casks in layers of dry sand; let the sand be perfectly dry, and each layer being covered keeps them from the air, from moisture, from frost, and from perishing, as the sand absorbs their moisture, which generally perishes them;

pippins have often been kept in this manner until mid-summer, and were as fresh then as when put in.
